List the datasets available in the Provider Data Catalog (PDC)

pdc_datasets.Rd

Provides the names, identifiers, and other associated metadata of datasets available from the CMS Provider Data Catalog (PDC) (https://data.cms.gov/provider-data/). This can be used to explore dataset contents/metadata and/or be used for identifying datasets to import in pdc_read.

Usage

pdc_datasets(topics = NULL)

Arguments

topics

A topic to list datasets for (see pdc_topics). If NULL, all datasets will be returned.

Value

A tibble containing dataset metadata. Specifically, an entry from the datasetid column can be used in pdc_read.

Examples

pdc_topics()
#>  [1] "Dialysis facilities"                   
#>  [2] "Doctors and clinicians"                
#>  [3] "Home health services"                  
#>  [4] "Hospice care"                          
#>  [5] "Hospitals"                             
#>  [6] "Inpatient rehabilitation facilities"   
#>  [7] "Long-term care hospitals"              
#>  [8] "Nursing homes including rehab services"
#>  [9] "Physician office visit costs"          
#> [10] "Supplier directory"                    
pdc_datasets("Hospitals")
